Can anyone else relate? 

It’s been years since we’ve really gone to a party. And when we got the invite to one this year, I really wanted to go. It was old friends who I hadn’t spent time with in a long time.

Then a few days before, the anxiety crept up. Who will be there? Will everyone be well? Will it be comfortable?

The day of, I couldn’t stop thinking about it. I don’t want to drive in the bad weather, I don’t want the kids to be bored, I don’t want Tim to feel like he doesn’t know anyone.

Now to formulate a plan to get out of it. 

But we go anyway.

We laughed, we cried, we ate, we “got the band back together”, we sang Christmas music, we wii bowled, we planned concerts, we promised continued lifetime friendships, WE HAD FUN!

If you can relate- I understand! Sheesh, it’s exhausting to enter back into social life again. Just do it! Just have fun! Just wear your stretchy pants and hoodie. You may just make some pretty cool memories 💚

#thebandisbacktogether #longlivewebbers #friendship #holidayparties

I had 2 different Monsteras, both were in their original nursery pots. I noticed recently that they were both looking droopy. It seemed like neither was really getting a good drink when I watered them. So I decided to repot them and both together in the same pot. 

A pot up was way past due because the roots were so coiled in their original pots (I feel bad). But this roomy orange pot is a perfect fit!

I repotted, gave it a good water, and now we need to find a new home for it😁
